@store_listing
This eye-care extension enables night mode by creating dark themes for websites on the fly. Catppuccin Reader inverts bright colors to make web pages high contrast and easier to read.

Adjust brightness, contrast, the sepia filter, font preferences. Enable dark mode on every web page or give websites a sepia tone. Enable or disable Catppuccin Reader for specific websites, automatically sync with system dark mode, or detect already dark websites and leave them unchanged.

Catppuccin Reader ships with the soothing pastel Catppuccin palette (Latte, Frappé, Macchiato, and Mocha) as selectable color schemes, alongside the classic presets.

Catppuccin Reader is a community fork of the open-source Dark Reader extension, restyled with the Catppuccin color scheme for both its own interface and the pages it darkens.

By installing the extension you agree to the terms in our repository: https://github.com/ImFromKazakstan/darkreader

Please disable similar extensions to avoid conflicts. Enjoy browsing!
